<doc id="761444" wikidata="Q7133987" url="?curid=761444" title="Paraclione">
<text>Paraclione is a genus of &quot;sea angels&quot;, small floating sea slugs, pelagic marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusks.

They are very small and gelatinous, mostly transparent, and they only have a shell during their embryonic stage. They can be found in the Atlantic Ocean.

== Species ==
Species in the genus &quot;Paraclione&quot; include:
*&quot;Paraclione flavescens&quot; (synonyms : &quot;Clionina aurantiaca&quot; ; &quot;Clionina flavescens&quot; )
*&quot;Paraclione longicaudata&quot; (synonyms : &quot;Clio longicaudata&quot; ; &quot;Clionina longicaudata&quot; 

==See also==
*Sea angel

